Date:    Mon, 16 Jul 90 16:21:07 -0400
From:    wack@csmes.ncsl.nist.gov (John Wack)
Subject: anti-viral product summary

I am putting together a list of anti-viral software products for a
large conference in October, and I would like to maintain the list and
make it available to whomever.  I see the list as objective, stating
basically what the product does and its features, but no subjective
opinions or categories of "best" or "okay" a la Consumer Reports.

To get a head start on this, I would GREATLY appreciate it if those
who have compiled similar lists would let me use their's as input to
mine.  Equally, I would like to receive product information from
vendors including those who deal only in shareware/freeware.  I will
make the list available for download and ftp, and notify this list
when it's complete.

Thanks in advance, John Wack - National Institute of Standards & Technology

