Subject: remac.exe and the Jerusalem Virus (PC)

I recently downloaded remac.zip from one of the ftp sites (I think
it was cc.ucsf.edu).  Anyhow when I unzipped the file I found out
that remac.exe had the Jersualem-B virus on it.  I used the MacAffee
scan and clean program, and the clean program worked just fine.  Got
rid of the virus and saved the program.  So if you have downloaded this
zip file check the exe file when you unzip it.

