Date:    Mon, 16 Jul 90 20:46:10 -0700
From:    dlo@questor.wimsey.bc.ca (David Lo)
Subject: Cleaning up after infection (PC)

If something in the boot sector is different, then it certain doesn't hurt
to look through it.  However, your explaination of a SYS with another
version of DOS is possible.  It is also possible that a buggy program
wrote something into the boot sector.  If there are sensitive or
important data, back them up, put a clean DOS back on the hard disk,
and hope for the best.  The more you try to play with a possible virus,
the more likely it'll do some harm.

