Date:    Wed, 18 Jul 90 18:02:00 -1200
From:    "Pat Cain, BB: +64 4 661231" <CS200CAP@ST1.VUW.AC.NZ>
Subject: ScanV64, Stoned and Stoned2. (PC)

/\_Someone writes...
>Question....
>How is the Stoned-II virus different from the Stoned virus?

It is different in that Stoned2 has different messages and is not
detected by most of the programs that detect the original Stoned
strain.

>I found a couple of my floppies that were "infected" in the boot
>sector with both.  Using VirusSCAN (V64), I got the following:
>Scanning for known viruses.
>Scanning boot sector of disk A:
>  Found Stoned-II Virus (S-2) in boot sector.
>  Found Stoned Virus (Stoned) in boot sector.

This occurs because of a mistake or misunderstanding between here
and McAfee Associates.  Simon sent a search string to McAfee that
occured in both strains.  McAfee took this to mean that the string
only occured in Stoned 2.  So if you have STONED in your boot sector
then SCAN64 will inform you that you have Stoned and Stoned2.
We suggest in the meantime that you use NOSTONE or FPROT111 which
both detect and remove the virus correctly.  NOSTONE currently is
the only program which detects double infections (which occur when
Stoned and Stoned2 clash with each other).

Simon has sent a new search string to McAfee that only occurs in
Stoned 2, so hopefully the next release of SCAN will be corrected.

Pat Cain
